        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(agent-sdk): add packaging spec + skeleton",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds the Agent SDK Packaging spec (v0.3 draft) and implementation skeleton, with hardened package path validation, schema-backed package config, quarantine read-only tool restrictions, shared network policy classification, CLI build wiring, and deterministic behavior proof output.\n\n## What's Included\n\n- `docs/specs/agent-sdk-packaging.md` — Full spec: manifest schema, integrity verification, secret scoping, network egress, mutable instruction policy, declarative upgrades, behavior harness, and config compiler requirements.\n- `packages/agent-sdk/` — TypeScript types, CLI commands, policy helpers, config compiler, test harness scaffold, examples, fixtures, and tests.\n- Agent package config schema support for the `agentPackages` compiler output block.\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n- **openclaw.integrity.json** (not lockfile) — content integrity, not dependency resolution.\n- **denyMutableInstructionFiles: true** — instruction files are prompt-layer code.\n- **Config compiler dry-run** — config output is now backed by the live config schema.\n- **No scripts, no hooks** — purely declarative upgrades.\n- **Fail-closed file handling** — package sources and workspace destinations are confined before copy, remove, pack, and validate operations.\n\n## Status\n\nDraft PR. Current branch includes the spec, implementation skeleton, hardened safety checks, targeted tests, and real checkout proof below.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: Agent SDK package workflow builds CLI entrypoints, validates package-owned files before copy/remove/hash operations, keeps quarantine tool access read-only, uses shared network special-use IP classification, validates emitted `agentPackages` config through schema support. The CLI `test` command now runs real validation, integrity, network, secret, tool, quarantine, compiler, and upgrade checks — no unconditional PASS output. Package policy fields (maxTokensPerTurn, allowedModels, tools, sandbox) are scoped under `agentPackages.packages.<name>.*` by default instead of leaking into `agents.defaults.*`. Non-canonical `source: \"gateway\"` SecretRef mappings are skipped with a compiler warning.\n\n- **Real environment tested**: Real local checkout at `/tmp/openclaw-agent-sdk-pr-worktree`, branch `feat/agent-sdk-packaging`, commit `f110b84284d3`, Node 22 / pnpm / tsdown 0.22 from the OpenClaw monorepo toolchain.\n\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\n# 1. Build the CLI\nnpx tsdown packages/agent-sdk/src/index.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/cli.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/hash.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/commands/pack.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/commands/validate.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/commands/enable.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/commands/disable.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/commands/test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/policy/secrets.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/policy/network.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/compiler.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/live.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/upgrade.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/quarantine/mutation.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/test.ts --no-config --platform node --format esm --dts --out-dir packages/agent-sdk/dist --clean\n\n# 2. Run the CLI test command against the valid-pack fixture\nnode packages/agent-sdk/dist/cli.mjs test packages/agent-sdk/src/__fixtures__/valid-pack\n\n# 3. Run the full agent-sdk test suite (8 files, 164 tests)\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/agent-sdk/src/pack.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/policy/policy.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/compiler.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/live.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/upgrade.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/quarantine/mutation.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/commands/enable.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/test.harness.test.ts\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix**: CLI test command output (real checks):\n\n```\n$ node packages/agent-sdk/dist/cli.mjs test packages/agent-sdk/src/__fixtures__/valid-pack\nAgent SDK behavior proof summary: PASS\nRequired proofs: 21\nPASS agent.manifest.valid\nPASS agent.integrity.valid\nPASS agent.integrity.mismatchFailsClosed\nPASS agent.installedState.valid\nPASS agent.installedState.driftQuarantines\nPASS agent.instructionFile.driftQuarantines\nPASS agent.mutableInstructionFile.deniedByPolicy\nPASS agent.requiredTool.missingFailsClosed\nPASS agent.requiredPlugin.missingFailsClosed\nPASS agent.requiredSecret.missingFailsClosed\nPASS agent.secretScope.enforced\nPASS agent.deniedTool.blocked\nPASS agent.externalContentToExec.blocked\nPASS agent.outbound.requiresApproval\nPASS agent.workspaceEscape.blocked\nPASS agent.schedule.disabledByDefault\nPASS agent.privateNetwork.blocked\nPASS agent.dnsRebinding.blocked\nPASS agent.sandbox.required\nPASS agent.configCompiler.dryRunValidates\nPASS agent.upgrade.permissionExpansionRequiresApproval\n```\n\nUnit tests (8 files, 164 tests):\n\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/agent-sdk/src/pack.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/policy/policy.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/compiler.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/live.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/compiler/upgrade.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/quarantine/mutation.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/commands/enable.test.ts packages/agent-sdk/src/test.harness.test.ts\n\n Test Files  8 passed (8)\n      Tests  164 passed (164)\n   Duration  9.98s\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: The CLI `test` command runs real validation (schema, integrity, mutable instruction policy), hash verification, network policy checks, secret scope enforcement, tool allow/deny policy, quarantine/mutation detection, compiler dry-run validation, and upgrade permission checks. Each proof ID is only marked PASS if the actual check passes. Package policy is scoped under `agentPackages.packages.<name>.*` by default, preventing silent global-default mutation. Non-canonical `gateway` SecretRefs are skipped with compiler warnings. All 164 unit tests pass across 8 test files.\n\n- **What was not tested**: No live gateway mutation, live schedule routing, live channel delivery, or real secret provider access was exercised. The `test` command validates the package fixture locally but does not install or enable the package in a live OpenClaw instance. Upgrade behavior is tested via unit tests only, not against a real running gateway.\n",
